
# ==========================================
#   Neural-Sync-AR - GUIDE
# ==========================================

Welcome to your AR Neural Interface project. This document explains how the system works, 
how to customize it, and how to deploy it to the web.

---

### 1. HOW TO USE THE INTERFACE
Once the system is running and you have clicked "INITIALIZE":

* LEFT HAND (The Command Hand):
    - 1 Finger Raised: Displays "AoA" (Blue)
    - 2 Fingers Raised: Displays "I AM HAMZA" (Yellow)
    - 3 Fingers Raised: Displays "DREAM BIG" (Pink)
    - 4 Fingers Raised: Displays "GOODBYE" (Green)
    - 5 Fingers (Open Palm): "CATCH READY" - Particles will wait for a command.

* RIGHT HAND (The Physical Hand):
    - Pointing/Moving: The particles will react to your index finger tip (Planar Repulse).
    - 5 Fingers (Open Palm): "NEBULA RIPPLE" - Creates a 3D wave effect through the particle field.

* THE ULTIMATE COMBO:
    - Raise both hands (5 fingers each) simultaneously to trigger the "Ultimate Combo" sphere.

---

### 2. HOW TO CHANGE THE NAME & TITLES
To rename the project from "HAMZA INTERFACE" to your new name:

1. Open the .html file in a text editor (like Notepad, VS Code, or Sublime).
2. Change the Browser Title:
   Look for: <title>HAMZA'S NEURAL INTERFACE v4.0</title>
   Change "HAMZA'S" to "YOURNAME'S".
3. Change the Start Screen:
   Look for: <h1>HAMZA INTERFACE v4.0</h1>
   Change it to your preferred project name.
4. Change the Gesture Text:
   Inside the <script>, look for: if(f===2){text='I AM HAMZA'; ...}
   Change 'I AM HAMZA' to any message you want to appear when you show 2 fingers.

---

### 3. CUSTOMIZING THE LOOK (CONFIG)
At the start of the <script> section, find the 'CONFIG' object:

* particleCount: 15000 (Increase for more detail, decrease if your PC lags).
* particleSize: 3.8 (Change this to make the "dots" bigger or smaller).
* lerpSpeed: 0.28 (Lower numbers make particles move slower/smoother).
* colors: Change the hex codes (e.g., 0x00FFFF) to change the HUD colors.

---

### 4. GITHUB UPLOAD (GITHUB PAGES)
To host this online for free:

1. Rename your main file to 'index.html'.
2. Go to GitHub.com and create a new repository (e.g., "neural-interface").
3. Upload 'index.html' and this 'README.txt'.
4. Go to Settings > Pages.
5. Set 'Branch' to 'Main' and click 'Save'.
6. GitHub will give you a link (e.g., https://username.github.io/neural-interface).

---

### 5. TROUBLESHOOTING
* BLANK SCREEN: This is usually because you are opening the file directly from your folder. 
    Browsers block cameras on 'file://' links. Use a local server (VS Code Live Server) 
    or upload it to GitHub to see it work.
* LAG: Reduce the 'particleCount' in the CONFIG section.
